    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Silver Grey Metallic. This example is powered by the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure dual-VANOS variable valve timing. The powertrain is mated to a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and the factory M-variable limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and rear subframe reinforcement to ensure chassis rigidity. The valvetrain has been recently shimmed to factory tolerances. While the exterior displays minor road-rash and patina consistent with an honest driver, the mechanicals are synchronized for peak performance, offering a linear power band up to the 8,000 RPM redline. Equipped with refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers, the handling remains sharp and predictable.",
